channel.title: Speed Changing?
channel.description: For some reason my computer speed keeps changing and it wont stay at the speed its suppose to be at.. its a 1.6GHZ Dual Core Laptop and it runs at 798 MHZ. And no you can't change process speed on laptops though bios.... So what the fuck is going on? I already try reformatting to and that didn't work.

It’s possible that the program you use to get the speed is fucking the data up. It might devide the 1.6 in 2, hence 800 (798) MHz

item.title: Speed Changing?
item.dc:creator: @The_Un-Named The Un-Named
item.description:
@The_Un-Named wrote:

The processor speed on laptops usually goes to half of it’s normal operating speed on battery power. If that’s causing it, you can set it so it uses full speed on battery power using NHC(among other things).
